HEADWORD: quarterback sneak
<hw>quarterback sneak</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Football)</fld> <def>A
play in football in which the quarterback carries the ball directly
ahead, immediately or shortly after receiving the snap, sometimes after
faking a handoff.</def>⟦br⟧
